---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Sentiment Analysis">
  <PageHeader
    title="Sentiment Analysis Guide"
    tags={["RunPod GPU", "A5000", "~250k reviews/hr"]}
  />

  <details>
    <summary>First-Time RunPod Setup</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <strong>Install uv</strong>
      <pre><code>curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh
source ~/.local/bin/env</code></pre>
      <strong>Clone & Setup</strong>
      <pre><code>cd /workspace
git clone https://&lt;YOUR_TOKEN&gt;@github.com/KBWW/skincare-analysis.git
cd skincare-analysis
uv sync</code></pre>
      <strong>Configure AWS</strong>
      <pre><code>cat > .env &lt;&lt; 'EOF'
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_secret
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=ap-southeast-1
S3_BUCKET=trendmix
EOF</code></pre>
      <strong>Verify GPU</strong>
      <pre><code>nvidia-smi
python -c "import torch; print(f'CUDA: &#123;torch.cuda.is_available()&#125;, Device: &#123;torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)&#125;')"</code></pre>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ── Tabs ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="tabs">
    <div class="tab-bar" role="tablist">
      <button class="tab-btn active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-tab="prep">1. preprocess</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="gpu">2. main_gpu</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="merge">3. merge</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="upload">4. upload</button>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 1. Preprocess ───────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel active" id="tab-prep" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">Keyword extraction using KoNLPy - runs locally or on EC2</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="prep">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="prep">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="prep">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="prep">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-prep-run">
        <strong>Production Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python preprocess_from_s3.py --date 260130</code></pre>
        <strong>With Custom Process Count</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python preprocess_from_s3.py --date 260130 --processes 8</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-prep-status">
        <strong>Check S3 Output</strong>
        <pre><code>aws s3 ls s3://trendmix/data/reviews/raw/260130/preprocessed_260130/</code></pre>
        <strong>View Manifest</strong>
        <pre><code>aws s3 cp s3://trendmix/data/reviews/raw/260130/preprocessed_260130/_manifest.json - | python -m json.tool</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-prep-config">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Argument</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>--date</td><td>required</td><td>Run ID (YYMMDD format)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--processes</td><td>4</td><td>Number of parallel processes</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--bucket</td><td>trendmix</td><td>S3 bucket name</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-prep-info">
        <ol>
          <li>Downloads raw review parquet files from S3</li>
          <li>Extracts Korean keywords using KoNLPy (Okt tokenizer)</li>
          <li>Categorizes words: effects, texture, satisfaction, skin_condition, etc.</li>
          <li>Uploads preprocessed data back to S3</li>
        </ol>
        <p><strong>Output columns:</strong> <code>keywords_effects</code>, <code>keywords_texture</code>, <code>keywords_satisfaction</code>, <code>keywords_skin_condition</code>, <code>keywords_product</code>, <code>keywords_economy</code>, <code>keywords_nouns</code>, <code>keywords_adjectives</code>, <code>keywords_verbs</code>, <code>keywords_adverbs</code></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 2. GPU ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-gpu" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">GPU sentiment analysis on RunPod - transformer model inference</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="gpu">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="gpu">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="gpu">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="gpu">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-gpu-run">
        <strong>Production Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd /workspace/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python main_gpu.py --date 260130</code></pre>
        <strong>Resume Interrupted Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd /workspace/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python main_gpu.py --date 260130 --resume</code></pre>
        <strong>Run in Background (tmux)</strong>
        <pre><code>tmux new-session -d -s sentiment 'cd /workspace/skincare-analysis && uv run python main_gpu.py --date 260130'</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-gpu-status">
        <strong>GPU Utilization</strong>
        <pre><code>watch -n 1 nvidia-smi</code></pre>
        <strong>Check S3 Output</strong>
        <pre><code>aws s3 ls s3://trendmix/data/reviews/raw/260130/processed_results_260130/</code></pre>
        <strong>View Progress (tmux)</strong>
        <pre><code>tmux attach -t sentiment</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-gpu-config">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Argument</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>--date</td><td>required</td><td>Run ID (YYMMDD format)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--resume</td><td>False</td><td>Resume from checkpoint</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--bucket</td><td>trendmix</td><td>S3 bucket name</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Model:</strong> <code>jhgan/ko-sroberta-multitask</code> · <strong>Batch:</strong> 512 · <strong>Chunk:</strong> 10,000</p>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-gpu-info">
        <ol>
          <li>Loads preprocessed reviews from S3</li>
          <li>Runs sentiment classification (positive/negative/neutral)</li>
          <li>Runs aspect-based sentiment (moisture, effectiveness, texture, absorption)</li>
          <li>Runs satisfaction classification (very/somewhat/unsatisfied)</li>
          <li>Uploads results to S3</li>
        </ol>
        <p><strong>Performance:</strong> ~400k reviews in ~30 min on RTX 4090 · Checkpoints every 10k reviews</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 3. Merge ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-merge" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">Merge new results with existing versioned DB data</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="merge">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="merge">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="merge">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="merge">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-merge-run">
        <strong>Production Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python merge_new_data_to_existing.py --date 260130</code></pre>
        <strong>With Custom Table Type</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python merge_new_data_to_existing.py --date 260130 --type product_review</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-merge-status">
        <strong>Check S3 Output</strong>
        <pre><code>aws s3 ls s3://trendmix/data/reviews/raw/260130/merged_results_260130/</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-merge-config">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Argument</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>--date</td><td>required</td><td>Run ID (YYMMDD format)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--type</td><td>product_review</td><td>Table type (looks up active version)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--bucket</td><td>trendmix</td><td>S3 bucket name</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-merge-info">
        <ol>
          <li>Loads sentiment results from S3 (<code>processed_results_&#123;date&#125;</code>)</li>
          <li>Queries <code>table_versions</code> to find the active versioned table</li>
          <li>Aggregates new data by <code>group_id</code> + <code>w_mon</code> (week)</li>
          <li>For overlapping groups: computes weighted average based on review counts</li>
          <li>Uploads merged result to S3</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 4. Upload ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-upload" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">Upload to PostgreSQL with table versioning</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="upload">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="upload">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="upload">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="upload">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-upload-run">
        <strong>Upload & Activate</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python upload_to_db.py --date 260130 --activate</code></pre>
        <strong>Upload Only (Don't Activate)</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python upload_to_db.py --date 260130</code></pre>
        <strong>Activate Specific Version</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python upload_to_db.py --activate-version product_review 7</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-upload-status">
        <strong>List All Versions</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/skincare-analysis && \
uv run python upload_to_db.py --list</code></pre>
        <strong>Query Active Version (SQL)</strong>
        <pre><code>SELECT table_name, version, row_count, created_at
FROM table_versions
WHERE table_type = 'product_review' AND is_active = TRUE;</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-upload-config">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Argument</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>--date</td><td>required</td><td>Run ID (YYMMDD format)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--type</td><td>product_review</td><td>Table type prefix</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--activate</td><td>False</td><td>Activate after upload</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--list</td><td></td><td>List all versions</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--activate-version TYPE VER</td><td></td><td>Activate specific version</td></tr>
            <tr><td>--cleanup TYPE [N]</td><td></td><td>Keep N most recent versions</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-upload-info">
        <ol>
          <li>Loads merged data from S3 (<code>merged_results_&#123;date&#125;</code>)</li>
          <li>Creates versioned table: <code>product_review_001</code>, <code>product_review_002</code>, …</li>
          <li>Registers in <code>table_versions</code> metadata table</li>
          <li>Optionally sets as active</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
